406
00:17:13.157 --> 00:17:15.117  position:40.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:89.66% 
I’ll get it.

407
00:17:17.578 --> 00:17:19.538  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:89.67% 
<i>Ay.</i> You okay?

408
00:17:19.622 --> 00:17:22.708  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Gloria!
Thank God you’re here.

409
00:17:22.792 --> 00:17:24.710  position:15.00%,start  align:start size:80.00%  line:84.33% 
Don’t worry.
I’m here too.

410
00:17:24.794 --> 00:17:27.129  position:15.00%,start  align:start size:80.00%  line:89.67% 
Who’s this?

411
00:17:27.213 --> 00:17:29.131  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:75.93% 
Wasn’t my fault.

412
00:17:27.213 --> 00:17:29.131  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:89.66% 
[ Scoffs ]

413
00:17:29.215 --> 00:17:32.217  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
I have seen you thread
the needle a million times.
You never miss.

414
00:17:32.301 --> 00:17:35.721  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:69.06% 
Yeah. I must be getting old.

415
00:17:32.301 --> 00:17:35.721  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:84.23% 
Why don’t you just admit it?
You never liked Phil.

416
00:17:35.805 --> 00:17:37.764  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Put that down.
You do not get a cookie.

417
00:17:37.848 --> 00:17:41.894  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
<i>I like Phil.</i>
<i>It’s just that sometimes</i>
<i>he tries too hard, you know?</i>

418
00:17:41.978 --> 00:17:44.563  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
And it’s just kind of–
[ Whispering ]
irritating.

419
00:17:44.647 --> 00:17:48.066  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
Okay, maybe he tries too hard
because you make
zero effort with him.

420
00:17:48.150 --> 00:17:50.402  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:79.00% 
You know what?
In the 16 years that
we’ve been married,

421
00:17:50.486 --> 00:17:53.906  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
have you one time told him
that you liked him?

422
00:17:53.990 --> 00:17:56.241  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:70.50% 
Not in those
exact words, no.

423
00:17:53.990 --> 00:17:56.241  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:10.00%  line:89.66% 
No.

424
00:17:56.325 --> 00:17:59.829  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:79.00% 
Not in any words, Dad.
How do you think
that makes me feel?

425
00:18:01.455 --> 00:18:03.582  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
You’ve never told
your son that you love him?

426
00:18:03.666 --> 00:18:06.084  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:84.33% 
Whoa, whoa.
When did we jump to love?

427
00:18:06.168 --> 00:18:08.170  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
And he’s technically
not my son.

428
00:18:08.254 --> 00:18:11.590  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:70.50% 
Ah. So that means that you
don’t love Manny either?

429
00:18:08.254 --> 00:18:11.590  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:89.66% 
Sure, I do.

430
00:18:11.674 --> 00:18:15.135  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
I mean, believe me, when I was
in that park, I really
wished Manny was there.

431
00:18:15.219 --> 00:18:20.265  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:79.00% 
For what? So that
you could fly the plane
into his head? Huh?

432
00:18:20.349 --> 00:18:23.602  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
Dad, thanks so much
for bringing Phil home.

433
00:18:23.686 --> 00:18:26.522  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
I found one of your little
flaps in his hair. So–

434
00:18:29.483 --> 00:18:31.568  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Actually, this is
called an aileron.

435
00:18:31.652 --> 00:18:33.863  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:45.00%  line:69.06% 
It controls the horizontal–

436
00:18:31.652 --> 00:18:33.863  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.23% 
Because that’s
what matters right now.

437
00:18:34.864 --> 00:18:36.782  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:89.67% 
Bye, Dad.

438
00:18:45.833 --> 00:18:49.462  position:40.00%,start  align:start size:55.00%  line:84.33% 
- Hey, Phil.
- <i>Jay.</i>

439
00:18:52.340 --> 00:18:54.049  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:69.06% 
[ Groans ]

440
00:18:52.340 --> 00:18:54.049  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.23% 
What are you,
made of china?

441
00:18:54.133 --> 00:18:56.426  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
<i>[ Groaning ]</i>

442
00:18:56.510 --> 00:19:00.597  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
Phil, I just want you
to know I’m sorry.

443
00:19:00.681 --> 00:19:03.350  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:84.33% 
And whether I, uh,
missed or you moved–

444
00:19:03.434 --> 00:19:06.186  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:75.93% 
I didn’t.

445
00:19:03.434 --> 00:19:06.186  position:75.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:89.66% 
Either way.

446
00:19:06.270 --> 00:19:08.480  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.33% 
I just want to say
that I like you.

447
00:19:08.564 --> 00:19:11.149  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:75.93% 
Really?

448
00:19:08.564 --> 00:19:11.149  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:10.00%  line:89.66% 
Yeah.

449
00:19:11.233 --> 00:19:13.235  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
What do you like about me?

450
00:19:16.447 --> 00:19:18.657  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:85.00%  line:89.67% 
You’re a nice guy.

451
00:19:18.741 --> 00:19:21.702  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:60.00%  line:89.67% 
Try real hard.

452
00:19:21.786 --> 00:19:23.870  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:89.67% 
I do.

453
00:19:23.954 --> 00:19:27.082  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:69.06% 
And you’re a good dad.

454
00:19:23.954 --> 00:19:27.082  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.23% 
Hey, I’m a good dad.
Come here.

455
00:19:27.166 --> 00:19:30.252  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:60.00%  line:84.33% 
Come here, you.
[ Groans ]

456
00:19:30.336 --> 00:19:34.214  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:70.50% 
This feels so right.
[ Groans ]

457
00:19:30.336 --> 00:19:34.214  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:89.66% 
<i>[ Door Opens ]</i>

458
00:19:34.298 --> 00:19:36.216  position:10.00%,start  align:start size:85.00%  line:89.67% 
What’s going on?

459
00:19:36.300 --> 00:19:40.095  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
There was a little accident,
but Jay’s telling Phil
how much he loves him.

460
00:19:40.179 --> 00:19:42.347  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
Oh. Well, that’s nice
for Phil.

461
00:19:42.431 --> 00:19:44.558  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
That’s great,
since he’s never said anything
like that to my boyfriend.

462
00:19:44.642 --> 00:19:46.601  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:60.00%  line:84.33% 
- Let it go.
- No, it’s not okay.

463
00:19:46.685 --> 00:19:49.521  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:79.00% 
No, Mitch is right.
Go in there too, Cam.
Come on.

464
00:19:49.605 --> 00:19:51.106  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:75.93% 
You’re kidding.

465
00:19:49.605 --> 00:19:51.106  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:10.00%  line:89.66% 
Okay.

466
00:19:51.190 --> 00:19:52.858  position:30.00%,start  align:start size:65.00%  line:84.33% 
- Jay!
- I’m gonna get this.

467
00:19:52.942 --> 00:19:54.568  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:75.93% 
Come on in, Cam.

468
00:19:52.942 --> 00:19:54.568  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:89.66% 
Just a little hug.

469
00:19:54.652 --> 00:19:56.069  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:60.00%  line:84.33% 
- Get in here.
- Say it.

470
00:19:56.153 --> 00:19:58.405  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:79.00% 
- [ Jay ]
Whoa! Hey, hey, hey!
- Say it! Say it!

471
00:19:58.489 --> 00:20:00.240  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:75.93% 
I like you too, Cam.

472
00:19:58.489 --> 00:20:00.240  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:10.00%  line:89.66% 
Aw!

473
00:20:00.324 --> 00:20:02.367  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:70.50% 
What do you like
about him?

474
00:20:00.324 --> 00:20:02.367  position:75.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:89.66% 
Oh, geez.

475
00:20:02.451 --> 00:20:03.994  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.33% 
Where did you get
that camera?

476
00:20:04.078 --> 00:20:06.705  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:70.50% 
Only the greatest store
on earth.

477
00:20:04.078 --> 00:20:06.705  position:75.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:89.66% 
[ Laughs ]

478
00:20:06.789 --> 00:20:09.291  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:84.33% 
[ Whispers ]
Thanks, Dad.

479
00:20:09.375 --> 00:20:10.917  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.33% 
Manny, picture!
Get in there too.

480
00:20:11.001 --> 00:20:13.170  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:70.50% 
<i>[ Phil ]</i>
<i>Get in here,</i> mi amigo.

481
00:20:11.001 --> 00:20:13.170  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:10.00%  line:89.66% 
Oh!

482
00:20:13.254 --> 00:20:15.297  position:70.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:84.33% 
<i>Stay still.</i>
<i>Say "cheese."</i>

483
00:20:15.381 --> 00:20:16.923  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:25.00%  line:69.06% 
Don’t push it.

484
00:20:15.381 --> 00:20:16.923  position:20.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:84.23% 
[ All ]
Cheese!

485
00:20:17.007 --> 00:20:18.091  position:80.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:89.67% 
Picture.

486
00:20:18.175 --> 00:20:20.093  position:40.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:69.06% 
Cheese!

487
00:20:18.175 --> 00:20:20.093  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:84.23% 
<i>[ Gloria ]</i>
<i>Cheese.</i> Queso.

488
00:20:20.177 --> 00:20:21.595  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:79.00% 
<i>[ Gloria Laughing ]</i>
 
[ Chattering, Laughing ]

489
00:20:21.679 --> 00:20:24.097  position:40.00%,start  align:start size:15.00%  line:70.50% 
[ Phil ]
Oh, boy!

490
00:20:21.679 --> 00:20:24.097  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:89.66% 
<i>[ Laughing Continues ]</i>

491
00:20:24.181 --> 00:20:26.725  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:79.00% 
[ Phil ]
Doesn’t it feel like these arms
could go around the world?

492
00:20:26.809 --> 00:20:28.769  position:5.00%,start  align:start size:90.00%  line:84.33% 
<i>[ Cameron Groans ]</i>
<i>I think I strained something.</i>

493
00:20:31.814 --> 00:20:34.441  position:65.00%,start  align:start size:30.00%  line:5.00% 
I always wanted
a daughter–

494
00:20:34.525 --> 00:20:36.443  position:35.00%,start  align:start size:60.00%  line:5.00% 
to dress her up
in pretty dresses,

495
00:20:36.527 --> 00:20:39.863  position:55.00%,start  align:start size:40.00%  line:5.00% 
do her hair,
her nails, her makeup.

496
00:20:39.947 --> 00:20:41.948  position:40.00%,start  align:start size:55.00%  line:5.00% 
[ Laughs ]

497
00:20:42.032 --> 00:20:45.494  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:5.00% 
No one knows this, but for
the first year of his life,

498
00:20:45.578 --> 00:20:48.914  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
I made up Manny like a girl
and told everybody
that he was my daughter.

499
00:20:48.998 --> 00:20:50.916  position:75.00%,start  align:start size:20.00%  line:89.67% 
[ Laughs ]

500
00:20:51.000 --> 00:20:52.918  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
<i>Ay,</i> but just
for a few times.

501
00:20:53.002 --> 00:20:54.628  position:60.00%,start  align:start size:35.00%  line:84.33% 
I didn’t want to mess
with his head.

502
00:20:54.712 --> 00:20:59.383  position:25.00%,start  align:start size:70.00%  line:79.00% 
When he found the pictures,
I told him that it was
his twin sister who died.

